226.Comment:
Access if via SSH secure shell.  Use external IP shown below, but password is restricted.
The Apoyar VPN infrastructure consists of one central VPN server (AMG) and several VPN Clients (RMG's) divided over customer sites and engineers. 
The AMG1 is a standard Apoyar OpenBSD build with amended isakmpd.policy &amp  isakmpd.conf files and server SSL certificates to make it a VPN server.
On AMG1 a DNS server is installed (www.tinydns.org) which controls name resolution on the VPN. The FQDN suffix chosen at install was \".apoyar\" and the current syntax for any node on the network is currently: &lt hostname&gt .&lt customername&gt .apoyar or in case of Apoyar Networks nodes: &lt hostname&gt .apoyar.
The DNS server is controlled by a text file data located in /services/tinydns/root/ and can be amended on the fly .
The website was developed with URL http://amg1.apoyar . This website lives on the Apache webserver which is installed on AMG1. The website files are located in the standard /var/www/htdocs/ directory and the configuration file  in the /var/www/conf/ directory.
